[Term]
id: EMRO:0000035
name: emotional valence
def: "A process quality that characterizes the degree of positivity or negativity of an emotion process." [] {IAO:0000119="https://dictionary.apa.org/emotional-valence"}
comment: According to cognitive appraisal theory, an individual's cognitive appraisal of a stimulus contributes to producing an emotion (with its corresponding emotional valence).
synonym: "hedonic tone" RELATED []
